article.headline: North Florida 70, Skidmore 43
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- James Grimball scored 19 points and added 11 rebounds to lead North Florida to a 70-43 win over Skidmore Thursday. The Ospreys jumped to a 17-2 lead in the first six minutes of the game and were never threatened. The Thoroughbreds cut the margin to eight at 25-17, but North Florida ran off 14 consecutive points for a 39-17 lead. North Florida held a 20-point margin at 41-21 at halftime. Grimball scored 15 of his points in the second half, including seven consecutive points during a 75-second stretch midway in the half when the Ospreys (2-10) stretched their lead to 54-31. Grimball's double-double was his second such feat in the last three games. The Ospreys connected on 25-of-51 shots for 49 percent, their second best average this year. They led by at least 18 points throughout the second half and held their largest lead of 29 points at 67-38 with 5:14 left in the game. Aaron Caruthers scored 16 points and Chris Timberlake added 15 for the Ospreys who committed just nine personal fouls in the game and ended a seven-game losing streak. Skidmore (1-6) was led by Jake Shechtman who came off the bench to score 9 points. The Thoroughbreds shot 34 percent (18-of-53) from the floor and converted just one free throw in seven attempts.
